25 class IdentifierFinder : public ExprTreeVisitor {
26 public:
27  IdentifierFinder(const ExpressionNode *root) : Root(root) {}
28 
29  void visitChildren(const ExpressionNode *en) {
30  for (int i = 0; i < en->getNumChildren(); i++)
31  en->getChild(i)->visit(this);
32  }
33 
34  virtual void visitIdentifierExpr(const IdentifierExpr *en) override {
35  if (en->getName() == NameToFind) {
36  Found = true;
37  // Note that if the identifiers expression seen so far are still
38  // compatible, set to 'Incompatible', i.e. we have to make sure that
39  // 'IdIncompatible' is never unset once it has been set to 'true'.
40  if (IdIncompatible == false)
41  IdIncompatible = Incompatible;
42  }
43  }
44 
45  bool getIdIncompatible() const { return IdIncompatible; }
46 
47 #define GEN_VISIT_COMPATIBLE_EXPR_NODE_IMPL(ExprName) \
48  virtual void visit##ExprName##Expr(const ExprName##Expr *en) override { \
49  visitChildren(en); \
50  }

76  virtual bool find(const std::string nameToFind) {
77  NameToFind = nameToFind;
78  Found = false;
79  IdIncompatible = false;
80  Incompatible = false;
81  Root->visit(this);
82  return Found;
